> Use fdisk or gdisk to create partitions with discoverable UUIDs
> Make partitions discoverable (no more fstab): https://systemd.io/DISCOVERABLE_PARTITIONS/ https://0pointer.net/blog/the-wondrous-world-of-discoverable-gpt-disk-images.html
> Use systemd-homed to maake a luks home directory: https://systemd.io/HOME_DIRECTORY/ https://www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/homectl.html#
> The ideal BTRFS Arch Linux installation: https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/qw02z5/the_ideal_btrfs_setup_on_arch_linux/
> More secure booting with systemd-boot & UEFI stubs: https://linderud.dev/blog/mkinitcpio-v31-and-uefi-stubs/
> How distros should handle encryption: https://0pointer.net/blog/authenticated-boot-and-disk-encryption-on-linux.html
